main event: Two unidentified objects were sighted moving at very high speeds, changing direction and elevation over Smithland, Iowa on August 13, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were moving very rapidly, changing direction and elevation.
The objects were observed by several adults and children.
The objects appeared to be astronomical in nature, but could not be positively identified.
The objects were in sight for several minutes, with one object appearing to rise to the southeast and another moving toward the northwest before reappearing near the zenith and then disappearing.
The objects never moved more than 1 foot in any direction.
